# PPT Harness Command Orchestrator

When the user message starts with `/ppt-creator`, `/ppt-review`, or `/ppt-publish`, execute the corresponding workflow below. You are the orchestrator -- you drive each phase using agent roles, skills, and tools available.

Read `AGENTS.md` for the full architecture (skills + agents), orchestration strategy, and file ownership matrix.

## `/ppt-creator <requirement>`

Execute these phases in order. Each phase dispatches to an agent role defined in `.agents/agents/`. Use the Task tool to dispatch subagents when beneficial (parallel dimensions, parts, or review categories). Fall back to sequential execution if subagents are not needed.

### Phase 1: Clarify (conditional)

Check if the requirement covers these dimensions:
- **Audience** (who will watch)
- **Scenario** (where/when presented)
- **Goal** (what action after watching)
- **Materials** (references, links, or notes -- optional but helpful)

If all present: proceed directly.
If any missing: ask concise follow-up questions, then proceed.

### Phase 2: Deep Research

Dispatch to **researcher agent** (`.agents/agents/researcher.md`):
- Read `.agents/skills/ppt-research/SKILL.md` for methodology
- WebSearch at least 3 dimensions, assign finding IDs (F1, F2, ...)
- If beneficial: parallelize dimension searches via Task tool
- Write `research-report.md` to artifacts directory

### Phase 3: Style Decision

Dispatch to **designer agent** (`.agents/agents/designer.md`):
- Read `.agents/skills/ppt-design-director/SKILL.md`
- Read `design-system/archetypes/`, `tokens/`, `reference-style.md`, `animation-strategy.md`
- Match archetype + token set + animation policy
- Write `style-plan.md` to artifacts directory

### Phase 4: Outline Generation

Dispatch to **architect agent** (`.agents/agents/architect.md`):
- Read `.agents/skills/ppt-outline-architect/SKILL.md`
- Apply Pyramid Principle, map parts to archetype narrative phases
- Each page gets `evidence_refs` linking to research finding IDs
- Save as `outline.json`, run `node scripts/validate-outline.js`

### Phase 5: Slides Composition

Dispatch to **composer agent** (`.agents/agents/composer.md`):
- Read `.agents/skills/ppt-slide-composer/SKILL.md` + `.agents/skills/slidev/SKILL.md`
- Read outline, style plan, page-templates, CSS design system
- If outline has 3+ parts and >= 12 pages: parallelize by part via Task tool
- Import `design-system/styles/global-tokens.css` and `page-classes.css` in headmatter
- Write `slides-<topic>.md`

### Phase 6: Preview

Dispatch to **engineer agent** (`.agents/agents/engineer.md`):
- Build: `npx slidev build <slides-file> --out <artifact-dir>/site`
- Serve: `node scripts/static-preview-server.js --dir=<artifact-dir>/site --port=3045`
- Return the preview URL to the user

### Phase 7: Deliver & Offer Review

After preview URL is returned:
- Ask the user: "是否需要运行质量审查？你也可以稍后用 `/ppt-review` 手动触发。"
- If yes: dispatch to **reviewer agent** (`.agents/agents/reviewer.md`), parallelize by category if beneficial
- If no: deliver as-is

### Output Format

After all phases complete, respond with:
- Artifact directory path
- Preview URL (clickable)
- Key files: research-report.md, style-plan.md, outline.json, slides-<topic>.md
- Export options reminder:

```
如需导出文件，可以：
- 导出 PPTX：npx slidev export <slides-file> --format pptx
- 导出 PDF：npx slidev export <slides-file>
- 导出 PNG：npx slidev export <slides-file> --format png
或者告诉我，我帮你执行导出。也可以用 /ppt-publish 发布到线上。
```

---

## `/ppt-review [slides-file]`

Dispatch to **reviewer agent** (`.agents/agents/reviewer.md`):
- Read `.agents/skills/ppt-review/SKILL.md`
- If `slides-file` is provided, review that specific file
- If not provided, review the most recently generated slides
- Run full checklist (overflow, narrative, factual, animation, design-system)
- Fix issues, rebuild preview, return updated URL

---

## `/ppt-publish [target]`

Dispatch to **engineer agent** (`.agents/agents/engineer.md`):
- Read `.agents/skills/ppt-publish/SKILL.md`
- If `target` is specified (`vercel` or `github-pages`): publish directly
- If `target` is missing: ask the user to choose
- Return the live site URL

---

## Gate Rules

- Phase N cannot start until Phase N-1 artifact exists
- Never fabricate research data -- use WebSearch
- Never skip outline validation
- Always return a preview URL after Phase 6
- Never publish without explicit user request
- Subagent dispatch is optional -- sequential single-agent is always valid
